definition.value: A glycosylgalactose consisting of beta-L-fucopyranose and D-galactopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
A glycosylmannose consisting of alpha-D-galactopyranose and alpha-D-mannopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
A glycosylglucopyranuronic acid consisting of beta-D-xylopyranose and D-glucopyranuronic acid residues joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
